**Abstract:**
Variant of the essay dated January 27, 1999 responding to John Paul II's encyclical Fides et Ratio. Argues Aquinas's conception of faith as intellectual assent is based on Aristotle's speculative knowledge rather than practical knowledge. Critiques the Pope's equivocal use of "philosophy" and questions whether philosophy can provide the benefits expected.

